    \code(`heq`); and \code(`veq`); draw horizontal and vertical, respectively, equality signs, so we can now draw a commutative “triangle”.
    \d-code(```
    \NCSq.diagram(fun tb -> (
      let emp = tb#emp in
      let obj = tb#obj in
      let harr = tb#harr in
      let varr = tb#varr in
      let heq = tb#heq in
      [[obj {${A}}; heq; obj {${A}}];
       [varr {} {${f}}; emp; varr {${h}} {}];
       [obj {${B}}; harr {} {${g}}; obj {${C}}]]));
```);%
